Standing in the middle of a pitch with a crowd of around 40,000 questioning your fitness and ability to get decisions right is a real test of mental strength.

Having a group of athletic, testosterone-fuelled players surrounding you, trying to intimidate and bully you into making a decision which favours them, is almost too much to bear.

And I am incredulous that Gary Neville and John Terry seem to think this harassment of referees is now somehow acceptable.

